Christmas trees

peanut butter cups (snack & miniature
sizes)
chocolate kisses
white chocolate (or candy melts)
white non-pariels

Melt the white chocolate (this will be the
“glue” that holds each layer together) and
put it in a squeeze bottle or ziptop bag with
a tiny cutoff corner.Set up an assembly line
-Tree trunk - upside down mini PB cup -
vvhite chocolate “glue”
-1st layer - upside down snack size PB cup
- drizzle white chocolate around the edges &
sprinkle with non-pariels